ratings.comment: It's been a few years, but Venes is memorable, if not effective. She came to mind because I'm now retaking courses for better exposure to the same material she "taught." My A wasn't enough, I wanted to learn the material. Is she knowledgeable? Yes. But she's not a great teacher of what she knows, and her tone can be borderline unprofessional.

Not a big fan. Dr. Venes certainly has the eye and credentials to teach this class. However, she corners you into an idea, thus draining any sense of creativity you may possess, and then gives you a bad grade. Tests are reasonably difficult and there is zero organization in this course, but Dr. V is very accessible via Skype and knows she is doing.
The whole class is about how to please her by abandoning your own style and adapting hers. Be ready to be confused.
